claim.claim-text:
1. A method for displaying a webpage in a tailored manner, comprising: 
matching a cookie identification to a customer number in a customer database table; 
matching a referral URL domain name in a referral URL database table to a source code; 
embedding said source code within a referral URL and matching said source code with said customer number; 
matching a source code with said customer number; 
matching said source code in a source code database table to an offer code; 
matching said offer code to corresponding offer text and an offer discount in an offer code database table; and 
displaying a webpage with said offer text and said offer discount.

4. A method for generating upsell products for display on a webpage, comprising: 
measuring a frequency of a combination of a product number and an upsell product number; 
entering said combination of said product number and said upsell product number and said frequency into an upsell product database table; 
referencing said upsell product database table for said product number; 
determining a rank for said upsell product number according to said frequency; and 
displaying said upsell product number according to said rank.

6. A method for delivering abandoned cart emails to a user wherein said user visits a website, comprising: 
referencing a visit detail database table for a cookie identification; 
creating a list including said cookie identification; 
removing said cookie identification from said list when said cookie identification is within a customer order detail database table; 
removing said cookie identification from said list according to an email sent flag in a shopping cart database table; 
matching said cookie identification to an email address in a customer database table; 
populating a template email with text and said email address; and 
sending said email to said user.

8. A method for delivering abandoned cart emails to a new user, wherein said user receives a solicitation email and visits a website for the first time, comprising: 
referencing an email number embedded in a referral URL enclosed in the solicitation email; 
matching said email number to an email address in a prospective customer database table; 
populating a customer database table with a cookie identification and said email address; 
referencing a visit detail database table for said cookie identification; 
creating a list including said cookie identification; 
removing said cookie identification from said list when said cookie identification is within a customer order detail database table; 
removing said cookie identification from said list according to an email sent flag in a shopping cart database table; 
matching said cookie identification to said email address in said customer database table; 
populating a template email with text and said email address; and 
sending said email to said user.

9. A method for registering a user for an e-newsletter on a webpage, comprising: 
displaying a text box for an email address from said user; 
recording said email address for a cookie identification and a customer number in a customer database table; 
referencing an offer code database table having promotional copy according to an offer code; and 
replacing said text box with said promotional copy on said webpage.

11. A method for populating categories of products for display within an e-commerce environment, comprising: 
determining a time period, wherein orders for said products occur during said time period; 
entering a quantity sold and a gross sales into a product sales database table for an order number within said orders; 
determining a sales factor rank based upon said gross sales; 
referencing a product number in said product sales database table; 
entering said sales factor rank for said product number into a category rank in a category database table; and 
displaying said product number according to said category rank.

15. A method for displaying an offline promotion on a webpage in an e-commerce environment, comprising: 
matching said customer number with a source code in a mailed database table; 
matching said source code with an offer code in a source code database table; 
matching said offer code with data in an offer code database table; and 
displaying said data on said webpage.
